{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Automated macOS Setup Assistant sequences for headless VM provisioning."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SetupAutomation","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SetupAutomation"},{"type":"text","text":" provides version-specific keyboard input sequences"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that walk through the macOS Setup Assistant without any human"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interaction. After the sequence completes, the VM has:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A user account (configurable, defaults to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"admin"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"admin"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SSH (Remote Login) enabled"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A UTC timezone configured"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"Design","anchor":"Design","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This follows the approach pioneered by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/cirruslabs\/tart"},{"text":" for Packer","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"boot_command","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" automation. The sequences have been verified against"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Tart’s working Packer plugin and adapted for direct use via the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Virtualization framework’s keyboard API.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Requirements","anchor":"Requirements","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtualMachineView"},{"type":"text","text":" must be attached to the VM (even"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen) for keyboard events to reach the guest."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The VM must be freshly installed from an IPSW — previously"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured VMs will not show the Setup Assistant."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Sequences are version-specific because Apple changes the Setup","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Assistant layout between major macOS releases."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Example","anchor":"Example","type":"heading","level":2},{"code":["guard SetupAutomation.isSupported(macOSVersion: 15) else {","    fatalError(\"No automation sequence for this version\")","}","","let steps = SetupAutomation.sequence(for: 15)","for step in steps {","    try await Task.sleep(for: .seconds(step.delay))","    await keyboardDriver.perform(step.action)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Adding Support for New macOS Versions","anchor":"Adding-Support-for-New-macOS-Versions","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When a new macOS version ships, its Setup Assistant layout must","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be mapped by hand:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Install the new macOS in a VM with a display attached.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Walk through Setup Assistant, recording each screen’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigation keys.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"in